casca (1.4.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Environments: group any number of apps and packages under a shared
    context (name, banner, icon, notes and creation defaults), with one
    launcher that opens a window listing everything inside it.
  * The Create button is now a menu: App, Package or Environment.
  * The main list shows environments alongside apps and packages, ready to
    edit or remove.

 -- OliverHub <282591028+oliverhubtech-source@users.noreply.github.com>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0300

casca (1.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Casca Store rebuilt in the GNOME Software style: featured apps carousel,
    colorful category tiles, Editor's Choice, and a detail page for each app
    with usage tags, the Bronze/Silver/Gold Casca seal, estimated disk
    savings, possible PC access, security info and company pages.
  * Region selector next to the search: detects the country automatically and
    filters marketplaces/news by region (or Global to see everything).
  * All new Store strings translated into the 20 supported languages.

 -- OliverHub <282591028+oliverhubtech-source@users.noreply.github.com>  Sat, 11 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0300

casca (1.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Background check for new releases (throttled, once a day at most), with
    a system notification and a one-click update for git-checkout installs.
  * About dialog now shows the license, a source code link, the release
    channel (release/beta/alpha), and a proper "What's New" page.

